        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_afon" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d1801e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>afon</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d1801e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>afonæ</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d1801e72"><sense xml:id="sense_d1801e73"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>время</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>time</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d1801e82"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пора</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>period</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d1801e91"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>срок</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>deadline</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:id="re_d1801e101">
                    <form xml:id="form_d1801e103" type="lemma"><orth>afonmæ</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d1801e106"><sense xml:id="sense_d1801e107"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>за это время</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>during this time</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d1801e116"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>до сих пор</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>still</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re xml:id="re_d1801e127">
                    <form xml:id="form_d1801e129" type="lemma"><orth>xorz afon</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d1801e132"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вовремя</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>in time</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re xml:id="re_d1801e144">
                    <form xml:id="form_d1801e146" type="lemma"><orth>ūcy afon</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d1801e149"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в ту пору</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>at that time</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re xml:id="re_d1801e160">
                    <form xml:id="form_d1801e162" type="lemma"><orth>afon ū!</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d1801e165"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пора!</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it's time!</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zaman"/>)</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zaman"/>)</note>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e188" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>afonæ næ kæni ærxonunmæ nostæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не считаешь ли, что пора сосватать невесту?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>don't you think it's time to marry off a bride?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>71</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e210" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ew afoni donmæ cæwuj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в одну пору (дня) он идет за водой</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he goes to fetch water at the same time (of the day)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>19%l11%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e232">
                        <quote>Qyzmydæjæn jæ aryn afon ærcyd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Кизмиде пришло время рожать</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>It's time for Kizmida to give birth</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e251">
                        <quote>ūj næ bæxy wasyn k˳y ū æmæ næ bælcconæn ærcæwyn afon k˳y næma
                            ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>это ржание нашего коня, а ведь нашему путнику (находящемуся в
                                отлучке) еще не пора приехать</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>this is the neigh of our horse, but it is not time to come for our
                                traveler (who is away)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 20</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e270">
                        <quote>sīxor afon k˳y ʽrcydīs, wæd ambyldta læppūty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда настало время обеда, он обыграл юношей</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when it was time for lunch, he beat the boys</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 30</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e290">
                        <quote>dæwias læppū acʼ afonmæ x˳yssa!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>чтобы мальчик твоего возраста спал до сих пор!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>so that a boy your age can still sleep!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1956 II
                            10</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e309" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>afonæ min æj næxemæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пора мне домой</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it is time for me to go home</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>121</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e331" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>i afonæ dær kud næ liǧdajdæ?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>время, разумеется, бежало</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>time of course was running</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e353">
                        <quote>afonmæ kænæ ærbadtysty kænæ næ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>к (данному) времени они или расселись, или нет</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they either sat down or not at the (proper) time</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            150</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e372" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>kæd ajfonmæ %i(sic! ← %i aj-afonmæ%i?)%i bomboli xussæntæbæl
                            xussuncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>может быть, они в данное время лежат на пуховых постелях</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>maybe they are currently lying on downy beds</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e394" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ew xed rævʒæ, innæ ba ajfonmæ dær eskæmæn nittudta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>один мост исправный, а другой к данному времени (вероятно) под
                                кем-нибудь провалился</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>one bridge is operational, and the other has probably failed under
                                someone by this time</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>295%l3%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e417">
                        <quote>afonmæ dær næ fæcæǧdyn k˳y q˳yd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>до сих пор надо было нас истребить</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it was necessary to exterminate us until now</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>91</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e436" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>eci fæsevæd ajfonmæ toppi næmugmæ sæ rew daruncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>та молодежь сейчас подставляет грудь под ружейную пулю</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>those young men are now putting their breasts under a gun bullet</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1937 I
                            35</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e458">
                        <quote>ænafon</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не-время</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>not-time</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (в смысле „позднее, ночное
                            время“)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (in the sense of “late, night
                            time”)</note>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            97</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e484">
                        <quote>ænafony wazæg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гость не вовремя</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>guest at the wrong time</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1801e499" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ænafonæ kænuj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>становится поздно</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it's getting late</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1937 I
                            35</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">%iafon%i ‘пора’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ‘год’
                    представляются двумя дериватами одного и того же корня %iāp%i- ‘достигать’ (см.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afun"/>); %iafon%i←*%iāpana%i; <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ← *%iapati%i-; словообразовательные отношения такие
                    же, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_widon"/> ← *%ividana%i-, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_widaʒ"/> ← *%ividātī%i-. B основе обоих слов лежит понятие
                    ‘достижение’, ‘завершение’, ‘окончание’; отсюда, с одной стороны, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ‘год’ как завершение космического и хозяйственного
                    цикла, с другой — %iafon%i как ‘урочный час’, ‘срок’; для последнего слова ср.
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e537" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āpāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>достижение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e545" xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>завершение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e551" xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>конец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e557" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>āpāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>достигающий цели</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда же, может быть,
                    германские слова для понятия ‘вечер’:<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e565" xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>æfen</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e571" xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>āband</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e576" xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Abend</w></mentioned>. %sФрейман%s (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хорезм. язык 67</biblScope></bibl>) и %sВaileу%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope>1956, стр. 120</biblScope></bibl>)
                    привлекают также <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e589" xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>ūfāniya</w>
                        <gloss><q>в то время</q></gloss></mentioned>. Остальные привлекаемые
                    %sBailey%s слова (<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e597" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āfənt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e603" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>phan-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e608" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>patouhan</w></mentioned>) семантически плохо вяжутся с %iafon%i.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">%iafon%i ‘period’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/>
                    ‘year’ are two derivatives of the same root %iāp%i- ‘reach’ (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afun"/>); %iafon%i←*%iāpana%i; <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ← *%iapati%i-; derivational relations are the same as
                    in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_widon"/> ← *%ividana%i-, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_widaʒ"/> ← *%ividātī%i-. Both words are based on the concept
                    of ‘achievement’, ‘completion’, ‘ending’; hence, on the one hand, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ‘year’ as ending of astronomic and business cycle, on
                    the other hand — %iafon%i as ‘due time’, ‘time period’; for the last word, cf.
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e629" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āpāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>achievement</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e637" xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>conclusion</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e643" xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>end</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e649" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>āpāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>achieving one's goal</q></gloss></mentioned>. Germanic words for
                    the notion ‘evening’ also probably belong here:<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e657" xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>æfen</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e663" xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>āband</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e668" xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Abend</w></mentioned>. %sFreiman%s (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="en">Xorezm. jazyk
                            67</biblScope></bibl>) and %sВaileу%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope>1956, стр. 120</biblScope></bibl>) also
                    cite <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e681" xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>ūfāniya</w>
                        <gloss><q>at that date</q></gloss></mentioned>. Other words that %sBailey%s
                    mentions (<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e689" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āfənt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e695" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>phan-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1801e700" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>patouhan</w></mentioned>) semantically do not match with %iafon%i.</etym>
